embedfield:
MongoDB long response time for particular search query

Case description:

  • I have very simple application (generated by Spring Initializr) connected to mongo DB.
  • Application task is to execute 2 queries (count and find) and return response. (mongo queries copied from [debug] logging in "MongoTemplate" that's why it shows $regularExpression rather than $regex)

The query:

{
  "$and": [
    {"domain": "test"},
    {"deleted": {"$ne": true}},
    {"specialItem": {"$ne": true}},
    {"$or": [
        {"textSearch": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QHANDLE\\E", "options": ""}}}
      ]
    },
    {
      "$or": [
        {"textSearch": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QMOUNT\\E", "options": ""}}}
      ]
    }
  ]
}

The code that generates aforementioned query:


@GetMapping("/demo") public ResponseEntity<String> demo() {
final List<org.springframework.data.mongodb.core.query.Criteria> criterias = new ArrayList<>();
    criterias.add(Criteria.where("domain").is("test"));
    criterias.add(Criteria.where("deleted").ne(true));
    criterias.add(Criteria.where("specialItem").ne(true));

    for (String word : List.of("handle", "mount")) {
        criterias.add(new Criteria().orOperator(
                Criteria.where("textSearch").regex("^.*" + Pattern.quote(word.toUpperCase()) + ".*")
        ));
    }

    final List<Criteria> orCriterias = new ArrayList<>();
    if(!orCriterias.isEmpty())
        criterias.add(new Criteria().orOperator(orCriterias));

    Query q = Query.query(new Criteria().andOperator(criterias.toArray(new Criteria[]{}))).with(Sort.by("domain", "deleted", "itemNumber"));
    q = q.skip(0).limit(20);
    long total = mongoOperations.count(q, DaoItem.class);
    final List<DaoItem> results = new ArrayList<>();
    List<DaoItem> daoItems = mongoOperations.find(q, DaoItem.class);

    results.addAll(daoItems);
    return ResponseEntity.ok("total: " + total + ", result: " + results); 
}
  • textSearch is an array of string, f.e.: ["00000001", "SMOUNT.", "TER.", "YYY", "1", "GLASS"]

Problem description:

Aforementioned query takes long time depending on the environment it's executed at.

Environments description:

  • mongo-java-driver|sync, version: 4.7.1
  • mongodb version different per environment ("major" the same)
  • spring-boot version: 3.1.3

I used JMeter in a loop to have a basic response time graph printed for each environment. Test was done for the same domain: test, on every environment. For each non-local env. ping <server address> gives time ~160 ms

I have four environments:

  • Local,
    • DB: mongo (v3.6.19) on docker with 747259 documents to look through,
    • Resources: m1 max + 64 GB,
    • Space: 530 GB available of 2 TB,
    • Response time: ~ 200 - 300 ms
  • Dev,
    • DB: mongo installed on machine (v3.6.8) with 747259 documents to look through,
    • Resources: Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5-2660 0 @ 2.20GHz + 5,78 GB,
    • Space: /dev/sda1 146G 9.3G 129G 7% /,
    • Response time: 3 - 8 s
  • QA,
    • DB: mongo (v3.6.8) installed on machine with 42491 documents to look through,
    • Resources: Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5-2660 0 @ 2.20GHz + 5,78 GB,
    • Space: /dev/sda1 146G 6.3G 132G 5% /
    • Response time: ~ 2 - 3 s.

My observations:

  • I set up a fresh mongodb instance on one of the remote servers (docker). Exported documents from "Dev" and imported in there. No one uses that database. When I connected to it, I've got response time similar to "Dev" env.
  • As partial matching is used in a query, index cannot be used. The winning plan is: IXSCAN (without textSearch of course)
  • Partial matching is required, hence I cannot use mongo text index.
  • MongoDB config on each environment is the same (default)
  • Query explain for Dev environment returns:
Documents Returned: 138
Index Keys Examined: 62448
Documents Examined: 62446
Actual Query Execution Time (ms): 2479
Sorted in Memory: no
Query used the following index: DOMAIN, DELETED SPECIALITEM

I changed the code, to generate following queries, and no change in response time was spotted:

{
  "$and": [
    {"domain": "test"},
    {"deleted": {"$ne": true}},
    {"specialItem": {"$ne": true}},
    {"$or": [
        {"searchWords": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QHANDLE\\E","options": ""}}},
        {"searchWords": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QMOUNT\\E","options": ""}}}
      ]
    }
  ]
}

{
  "$and": [
    {"domain": "test"},
    {"deleted": {"$ne": true}},
    {"specialItem": {"$ne": true}},
    {"searchWords": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QHANDLE\\E","options": ""}}},
    {"searchWords": {"$regularExpression": {"pattern": "\\QMOUNT\\E","options": ""}}}
    }
  ]
}

Here is the explain result:

Query:

{
    "domain": "test",
    "deleted": {"$ne": true},
    "specialItem": {"$ne": true},
    "searchWords": {"$regex": "(HANDLE|MOUNT)"}
}

explain result (short):

Documents Returned: 2853 Index Keys Examined: 76606 Documents Examined: 76606 Actual Query Execution Time (ms): 1391 Sorted in Memory: no Query used the following index: DOMAIN ITEMNO
--- 
FETCH nReturned: 2853 Execution Time: 974ms IXSCAN nReturned: 76606 Execution Time: 358ms Index Name: domain_-1_itemNo_-1 Multi Key Index: no

My question

  • I am a beginner when it comes to mongo, so I run out of options.
  • What other direction I could go when it comes to that query, to debug why it's taking so long on "Dev" environment?
  • I'm considering moving search mechanism to elasticsearch, but still, that particular question is about mongo, what I could do to reduce the response time to ~2s f.e. on the Dev env?
